title: Swimming: Montclair YMCA season set to kick off Saturday
text:
Swimming: Montclair YMCA season set to kick off Saturday October 22, 2015 Last updated: Thursday, October 22, 2015, 12:32 AM The Montclair Times Print 
YMCA swim season starts this weekend 
The YMCA of Montclair Dolphins swim team kicks off its 2015-16 season this Saturday, Oct. 24, with their Black/Red Meet scrimmage for new and younger swimmers. 
The Dolphins are also celebrating the accomplishments of standout Cha O'Leary, a senior at Montclair High School. 
O'Leary recently announced her committment to swim at Yale University next winter, while she was also named a USA Swimming Scholastic All-American for the second year in a row. 
Coming off of a long-course season full of notable accomplishments, the Dolphins are anxious to get the season going and work on the skills that will yield more success come the short-course championship season. 
A YMCA national champion in the 100- and 200-meter breaststroke this past summer, O'Leary is also a two-time NJSIAA high school champion in the 100-yard breaststroke. 
The Dolphins recorded 38 new team all-time best times top-10 times during the 2015 long-course season, which ended in August. They included nine from Charles Cobbertt, six from Hannah O'Halloran, five from O'Leary, four from Emily O'Halloran, three from Sean Severson, two from each of Avery Best, Sam Kirkman, Kai Michaud and Catherine Rodgers and one each from Jordan Shaffer, Carter Travia and Tommy Wolinski. 
There were more current top-10 times posted in 2015 than in any year in Dolphins history except 2009.
